			<div>Hi all!</div><div></div><div>My last topic got delted due to boardrule issues. I am not exactly sure what rules it was against, but anyways here is a new try :-) Hopefully nothing will be against the boardrules this time.</div><div></div><div>Backround: Some macroing guy is making me angry (i hate macroing) and i was told, macroing is ok as long as you are at your PC and react. So far so good. So here are just a few yes / no questions to make sure i fully understand whats ok and whats considered against the rules.</div><div></div><div></div><div>1. Macroing is allowed as long as you are at the PC? yes / no</div><div>2. is 3rd party software allowed? yes / no</div><div>3. if answer to question 1 is YES, but a 3rd party software is used / needed for it, is it still allowed? yes / no</div><div>4. is there a way WITHOUT 3rd party software to autofollow mobs? yes / no</div><div>5. is there a way to autorun in a circle / triangle / whatever without a 3rd party programm? yes / no</div><div>6. is there a way to face a mob automatically while running (alternate way to &quot;autofollow kinda i guess), without the use of 3rd party software? yes / no</div><div></div><div></div><div>OK, thats it with my questions. I hope this does not go against board rules as well <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-indifferent.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></div><div></div><div>What id like to see is a responce from someone &quot;who has to know for sure&quot; read... anyone from SOE of corse. If you can answer any of the above questions with a &quot;no&quot; there issomeone breaking the rules for monthson Bristlebane *shrug*.</div><div></div><div>Id like to know this because i do not want to report someone thats fine with the rules. My own ethic / logic tells me he is breaking em hardcore, but i was also sure macroing in itself was against rules and i was wrong as well lol.</div><div></div><div>Moderators: if this questions are against rules, pls let me know what exactly i have to change. Or give me the answers pretty pls? <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> Can't be a problem to let people know whats right and wrong, right? <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></div>	
