		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>There are two types of macroing.&nbsp; There is the type that is built into the game and there is the type that uses 3rd party software.&nbsp; So, game-supported macroing is allowed when you are at keyboard.&nbsp; Then there is the type that uses a program with macro in its name, those "macros" are not allowed.&nbsp; Keyboards that allow you to set up macros may be a grey area, I believe they are ok if you are actually at the keyboard (and not with your back turned watching tv).</P>
<P>Third Party Software that does not change gameplay or taps into the server side of things is allowed.&nbsp; So that would be things like 3rd party speech programs or instant messaging or alternate MP3 players.</P>
<P>There is no way that I know of in game and within the EULA to autofollow mobs.&nbsp;</P>
<P>There are ways to run/swim in circles by sticking a matchstick or something into your number pad.&nbsp; As with the keyboards with macros built in, I think this is one of those that is ok if you are at the keyboard.&nbsp; </P>
<P>You can certainly follow a mob very well by simply following it.&nbsp; However there is no command that I know of (just as in autofollowing a mob) to do it automatically.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>02-04-2006</span> <span class=time_text>01:29 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
				&nbsp;
				
