		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>1. Macroing is allowed as long as you are at the PC? yes... Macros themselves are not illegal, and in fact encouraged in game. However, third party programs that create and carry out&nbsp;macros&nbsp;that are not a natural function of the game are illegal (see&nbsp;#2).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. is 3rd party software allowed? yes, as long as it does not ALTER the information going to or coming from your computer and SOE.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. if answer to question 1 is YES, but a 3rd party software is used / needed for it, is it still allowed? yes... example would be a Belkin Nostromo speedpad, which was one of a ranger's only options before the archery autoattack function was introduced.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. is there a way WITHOUT 3rd party software to autofollow mobs? no</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5. is there a way to autorun in a circle / triangle / whatever without a 3rd party programm? not a precise, repeated pattern, as you described in the original post. I have seen some experienced quad kiters do some very nice pathing runs though.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>6. is there a way to face a mob automatically while running (alternate way to "autofollow kinda i guess), without the use of 3rd party software? no</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I read your first post about this issue. I do believe you are witnessing cheating. Kudos to you for standing up for what you believe.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>	
