			>
			<div></div><div>I &quot;accidentally&quot; discovered a way to create what might be considered an &quot;autorun&quot; macro by remapping my keyboard so that W, S, A, and D can be used to move my character around (sometimes keeping my hands so close together between the right of my keyboard and mytrackballmakes them a little crampy).</div><div></div><div>So anyway, one daymy char isrunningbetween points A and B,and I start typing out a message to someone, and then I realize that my char won't stop running. With the mousefocus on the message window, the letter keys no longer affect the movement of my characters, so it just keeps doing the last instruction it got from the keys. I can still &quot;steer&quot; using the left and right arrow keys, but as long as I don't engage the forward or backwards keys, my chars will keep running, swimming, moving forwards, until I stop them.</div><div></div><div>Since I am at my keyboard, I am using legitimatein-game options and settings,and only using it to save me from having to keep a key constantly depressedwhen I am moving great distances,I seeno violations. </div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							The one true constant in the universe is change. <br>Why so many people choose to view this as a personal insult is beyond me.
