		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<span><blockquote><hr>Zaradum wrote:&nbsp;<div>1. Macroing is allowed as long as you are at the PC? <b>The
assumptions that "attended macroing" would be allowed originates, as
far as I know, from Ultima Online. In EQ it always has been very
simple: There is no macroing allowed. Period. Of course the GM/Guide
has no way of knowing if you are pressing buttons yourself or if it is
a macro running, that's why they send you a tell. If you fail to
respond the assumption is that you are in fact macroing. There is no
visible difference between mashing buttons and macroing.<br>
  <br>
  </b></div><div>2. is 3rd party software allowed? <b>No, that's specifically prohibited in the EULA.<br>
  <br>
  </b></div><div>3. if answer to question 1 is YES, but a 3rd party software is used / needed for it, is it still allowed? <b>No, see above.<br>
  <br>
  </b></div><div>4. is there a way WITHOUT 3rd party software to autofollow mobs? <b>No, there isn't.<br>
  <br>
  </b></div><div>5. is there a way to autorun in a circle / triangle / whatever without a 3rd party programm? <b>Maybe with some very elaborated programmable joypad. It 'could' be possible.<br>
  <br>
  </b></div><div>6. is there a way to face a mob automatically while
running (alternate way to "autofollow kinda i guess), without the use
of 3rd party software? <b>No, there isn't.</b><br>
</div><hr></blockquote><br></span><div></div>
