		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Samanna wrote:<BR><BR>1. Macroing is not allowed.<BR>2. Game pad controllers that have built in button sequencing is allowed.<BR><BR><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Bard&amp;message.id=623" target=_blank><B>Original Post</B></A><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Number two actually means that someone could quite easily run in a triangle or square, very precisely without using a macro, if they have a gamepad, or programmable keyboard, that allows key sequencing. Just setup a loop that goes forwardarrow x seconds, leftarrow y secs, forwardarrow, leftarrow, etc.</P>
<P>Now, beyond that, I know some people who use scripts they have written to make multiboxing easier. I'm not sure where they fit into this, but essentially, they rig something up so their main has a hotkey, that sends a tell to their box, saying heal me. The box then /rtars them and casts heal. I don't know if that is a gray area, or if that is the type of macro that is prohibited. The guy I know who does it, says it just keeps him from having to tab to heal.<BR></P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>Absor wrote: <br> Yes, I will nerf this <br><br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
							</div>
								
