			>
			<div></div><p>I just wouldn't bother with using any macro program. If I was a GM, my first assumption if you were using any program like that would be to assume that you are abusing the EQ system in someway. They ban you and lose what, 15 bucks a month? Not a big loss to them.</p><p>Something that I think is funny though, is the way SoE tends to copy alot of the &quot;bad programs&quot; out there. I am not going to use any names but, the ingame mapping system for EQ for one. Used to be if you had a ingame map, even if it was without mob radar, and they knew about it, they would jack your account.</p><p>Player Profiles. It took them all this time to set up a player profile system, and it acts just like one of the popular ones that everyone uses. Even now I have heard rumor that the Eq Players thing isn't working because of a series of account leaks and what not. Not sure how true this is but still, why risk it?</p><p>My thing, why make a macro to run in a circle. Grab your hackiesack, and stick it on your keyboard... lol... positioned right, you can run in circles all day. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></p><p>I heard rumors too that SoE had a echoing program for popping in and out of zones to do these tests that would bounce back info to them letting them know if your being naughty or nice. Again, just something I heard.</p><p>Devs, you agree with me? Just don't use the stuff except what was intended for you? Seriously cause otherwise your just asking for trouble. Besides, what the heck is the point of playing the game if your not going to play it?</p>
