<DIV>1. Macroing is allowed as long as you are at the PC? yes / <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>no</FONT><FONT color=#ff0000> - not really.&nbsp; The game offers limited ways to macro using hot keys that you can continually hit over and over again.</FONT></STRONG>&nbsp; -<EM>Or in other, less round-about words, YES, using EQ's macro system.</EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM></EM>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. is 3rd party software allowed? yes / <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>no </STRONG></FONT><EM>-Teamspeak and other communication programs are third party, third party timers, parsers, WinEQ, software for gamepads and keyboards, the operating system, etc...There are&nbsp;lots of 3rd party programs that do not alter the data stream to or from the end user that have always been accepted as "allowed", has official SOE policy changed on these things?</EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM></EM>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. if answer to question 1 is YES, but a 3rd party software is used / needed for it, is it still allowed? yes / <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>no </STRONG></FONT><EM>-There have been posts by developers in the past stating that programmable keypads and controllers are acceptable in EQ, so the programs that run these peripheral devices would have to be allowed, right?</EM></DIV>
