<HR>
RhumbaKween wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Samanna wrote:<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Stealza-PWHP wrote:<BR><BR>I believe the EULA allows for ATTENDED macros from third party programs.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Rytan_the_Wyrmlord wrote:<BR><BR>Actually, the statement I made was directly in reference to game pad controllers that have built in button sequencing. I'm not sure where everyone got the idea that I said macroing was ok, as it certainly is not.<BR><BR>-Ryan<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>I've read (and quoted) that statement repeatedly since it was written almost two years ago, and the message I always come away with is this:<BR><BR>1. Macroing is not allowed.<BR>2. Game pad controllers that have built in button sequencing is allowed.<BR><BR><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Bard&amp;message.id=623" target=_blank><B>Original Post</B></A><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><BR>I thought someone got&nbsp;suspended awhile back for using a gamepad for foraging?</P>
<P>Here is the thread. It was the autofire program which does exactly the same thing as a game pad so you could not tell the difference.</P>
<P><A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=9139&amp;page=1" target=_blank>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=9139&amp;page=1</A></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>I think&nbsp; the key issue there was the fact that his foraging was unattended. Whether you are using the autofire program or the gamepad you need to be sitting at the keyboard so you can respond to a GM if they send a tell. They have no way of knowing which you are using, but if you don't reply to them, they will know it's unattended and that breaks the EULA in either case.
